  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Life-saving food/cash assistance to 18,000 undocumented Afghan returnees from Iran</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project objective is to save lives and protect livelihoods through the provision of life-saving food/cash assistance to 18,000 male and female vulnerable undocumented returnees over 9 months. CERF funds will ensure returnees receive a 30-day food ration upon their arrival. This food ration will provide the daily recommended kilocalorie intake of 2,100 kcal/person/day. In addition, any families who travel on from the border to the western and southern regions will also receive a two-month cash assistance to cover for their most urgent food and no-food needs in the places where they settle.</narrative>
  </description>
